article.headline: Tennessee Tech 92, Jacksonville 74
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Willie Jenkins scored 27 points and Tennessee Tech raced out to a big first-half lead in a 92-74 victory over Jacksonville on Sunday. Milone Clark scored 13 points and Derek Stribling added 12 points and eight rebounds for the Golden Eagles (4-4). Antonio Cool led the Dolphins (4-3) with 17 points, while David Lee had 14 and Haminn Quaintance 13. Jason Prince added 11 points and Jesse Kimbrough 10. Both teams shot 46 percent from the field but Tennessee Tech won the battle at the free-throw line, hitting 31 of 34 chances while Jacksonville shot just 15 of 27. After Prince hit a 3-pointer with 12:52 to play in the first half to cut Tennessee Tech's lead to 19-16, the Golden Eagles went on a 11-0 run over the next four minutes to take control of the game. Antjuan Koger hit two 3-pointers during the run. The Golden Eagles stretched their lead to 21 points with 2:29 left in the half on two free throws by Jenkins, and took a 53-31 lead to halftime.
